        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} dealership. After some back and forth, since the employee was only covering for vacation, we finally got started. </p>
        <p> First, we drove towards Immenstadt, or rather, right back out. We headed to the Alpsee Coaster. This is Germany's longest summer toboggan run with a length of 2.8 km and loads of curves. This was already our third or fourth attempt, but it was either closed due to rain or too crowded. But today we were lucky. There was no one there and the sun was shining. So we first took the cable car up the mountain. The view was great, and from the chairlift, we could see some beautiful and interesting hiking trails (note to self: remember for later adventures). When we arrived at the top, we discovered there was even an alpaca farm up there with many cute alpacas in the meadows. There's even a short circular hiking trail around the enclosure. We took advantage of this opportunity right away, and then we went down the mountain on the toboggan run at breakneck speed. Once at the bottom, we had to take a short break to let our adrenaline levels return to normal. It's a really nice toboggan run that can compete with the one in Mieders/Stubai Valley. </p>
        <p> After a drink, we decided to quickly head to the Mittag (mountain) to eat at an alpine hut that we knew from the TV show "WDR Wunderschön". Unfortunately, this cable car was also supposed to close at 4:30 PM. Well, it was 2:30 PM, so we should make it. </p>

