        <p> However, after it took us over 30 minutes to get up the mountain and we then discovered that the alpine hut was another 30-minute walk away, we decided to just have a small snack at the summit station and then prefer to grill at the campsite. So we enjoyed the view in all directions and saw several more interesting hiking trails on another mountain, which we saved in our phones for the next few days. </p>
        <p> On the way back, we stopped for a walk in Sonthofen. Steffi wanted to check Fielmann again for prescription sunglasses. Unfortunately, no luck there, and we promptly found ourselves in a café again, enjoying the day and a hot chocolate. </p>
        <p> Back in Oberstdorf, it was time to do some shopping and head to the campsite for grilling. Eventually, the dishes called, which took extra long because we had a long chat with Miriam, a neighbor. </p>
